Glenmark, Jain Irrigation, Thermax Fall After MSCI Index Removal

-- B y   A d i   N a r a y a n
-- 
2011-02-28T13:03:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/glenmark-jain-irrigation-thermax-fall-after-msci-index-removal.html
  Glenmark Pharmaceuticals Ltd .,  Jain
Irrigation Systems Ltd ., and Thermax Ltd. fell after the stocks
ceased to be part of the  MSCI India Index  today.  “Funds tracking this MSCI index would have sold the stocks
today,” Chirag Dagli, vice president of research at ICICI
Securities Ltd. in Mumbai, said in a phone interview.  Glenmark fell 9.9 percent to 251.3 rupees at the 3:30 p.m.
close in Mumbai, the steepest decline since Aug. 19 2009. Jain
Irrigation declined 7.3 percent to 182.95 rupees. Thermax, a
power equipment maker, retreated 7.3 percent to 556.15 rupees.
The Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive index rose 0.7 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adi Narayan in Mumbai at 
